node.text:
Vanilla Bean Flan Cake, a fluffy sponge cake layer topped with a delicious vanilla bean layer made from pastry cream, that is baked until the top of the pastry cream turns lovely brown.
Flan is one of my all-time favorites Frech pastries. The original Flan as seen in Paris is most often made with a pâte brisée sucrée bottom, I have never been a fan of that kind of bottom, In this recipe, I use a sponge cake bottom instead. 

This Flan cake is so delicious in taste and tastes even better the day after.

node.text:
This Scandinavia almond Coffee/Daim ice cream cake is my favorite cake/dessert. If someone asks me Manuela what is your favorite cake? This is that cake.

This ice cream cake has a gooey almonds crust, the crust is made with whipped meringues and almonds, perfect if you need to make a cake that is gluten-free.

The coffee/Daim ice cream is super simple to make and the flavors are just amazing. Even if you don't drink coffee, You are going to love this Ice Cream Cake, the coffee just gives the ice cream that little it factor.

The combination of the gooey almond crust and the coffee ice cream combined with Crushed Daim Candy is so incredibly delicious and special and perfect for any party.
 

I hope you love this ice cream as much as I do, it is so good!

#icecreamcake #myfavoritecake #daimcake #daimcandy #glutenfree #glutenfreerecipes #love #yummy #sweettooth #eats #recipe #kake #søte #canon #macrophotography

node.text:
Pillow soft and fluffy sweet buns with a creamy and dreamy custard center and juicy strawberries.

After it is baked it is drizzled with a simple glaze and coconut.

The sweet dough is made with Greek yogurt, resulting in a super soft dough, I proof the dough in the fridge overnight, or you can proof the dough for just a few hours) proofing the dough overnight makes the sweet buns just pillow-soft.

The creamy custard is the star in this recipe, it is made with real vanilla bean, heavy cream for extra richness, whole milk, sugar, cornstarch, lots of egg yolks to get this beautiful pale yellow color, and butter. After the custard is cooked, I pour the warm custard into my blender, and there is where the magic happens, there is so much richness and the vanilla flavor it is just amazing and having the custard in the blender for just a few seconds makes such a difference in texture. It is so creamy.

Adding fresh bright red strawberries ( when they are in season) into the center of the creamy custard makes for one amazing sweet bun, After the buns are baked it is drizzled with a sugar glaze and drizzles with desiccated Coconut. 

If you love sweet rolls, pastry cream, strawberries, glaze, and coconut you're going to love this one.

Two fluffy vanilla sponge cake layers, filled with a light and dreamy Greek Yogurt Strawberry & Passion fruit filling. The top is drizzled with a juicy passion fruit glaze.

This cake is what summer dreams are made of.

The whipped Yogurt frosting is light and so dreamy it is combined with fresh passion fruit pulp/juice and seeds and bright red strawberries especially when they are in season. This filling is so incredibly juicy and has the most amazing flavors of summer.
 

Instead of covering the cake with frosting, I decided to cover the second layer with a passion fruit glaze Instead, sometimes less is more.

The glaze is so juicy and bursting with passion fruit flavor a perfect match to the rest of the cake.
 

This is such a great combo, absolute homemade deliciousness!

I hope you fall in love with the cake and the flavors of this fluffy cake

node.text:
If you are looking for a show-stopping banana cheesecake, look no further.
This one features a crust made of frosties cereal, rather than predictable graham crackers but if you like your cheesecake to have a more classic crust use graham crackers instead.
On top of the crust is a dreamy banana cheesecake, that is super smooth in texture, it has tons of banana and vanilla flavor.

To get this delicious banana flavor in your cheesecake batter, I steep warm cream and vanilla bean paste together with sliced very ripe bananas in the fridge overnight. It is important you use very ripe bananas (those spotty brown bananas is perfect)  to get the ultimate banana flavor in your banana cheesecake

I hope You love this one as much as I do.

node.text:
When it comes to milkshakes, the banana flavor is my all-time favorite, I just love this nostalgic banana flavor and love incorporating the natural sweet banana flavor often into my frostings, cakes, cupcakes, and cheesecakes.
 

This Banana Milkshake - Whipped mascarpone is so delicious, it tastes just like an old-fashioned milkshake that you get at a diner, it is made with a banana-vanilla infused cream, using heavy cream, vanilla bean pod/seeds, and very ripe banana slices. I steep all these overnight in the fridge. resulting in the most amazing dreamy banana flavor in your frosting, tasting just like an old-fashion banana milkshake.

To get an intense banana flavor in your mascarpone it is so important you use very ripe bananas (those spotty brown bananas are perfect) to get the ultimate banana flavor.

The combination of banana-vanilla cream and mascarpone makes this frosting more stable/firmer and even more creamy and dreamy in taste, you just have to try it to understand how it tastes.

You can use this frosting as a filling in your cakes, or pipe on top of your cupcakes, or serve it on waffles, or on top of your ice cream, it is so delicious.

The bananas are sweet by themself, so you could easily make this frosting recipe sugar-free as it is just as delicious without the little amount of sugar I have added.
